<br>
But, I must say, people are easy to jump on the &quot;he's a gimp tank, because his gear sucks&quot; bandwagon. Sure, it's kinda mediocre, and I'm sure Ritch's agro doesn't even compare to a lot of other warriors on the server some people might be used to playing with.<br>
<br>
But all the talk about &quot;you have to have XX amount of hp and XX AC&quot; just to be able to group in a certain zone, really shows your narrowmindness regarding grouping. It does reminds me a lot of Velks, yeah, where rogues thought it was a really swell idea to let them tank, because they had 50 more ac than me.<br>
<br>
It's really pathetic to blame the close calls on healing on the tank. You knew his hp, if you really really are so narrowminded (or poor excuse for a cleric) and think that isn't enough for PoV, you shouldn't have taken him as a tank. I fought the PoN spiders a lot, which is comparable to PoV, with just shammie and druid buffs - I didn't even break 6k.<br>
<br>
A good cleric should be able to keep a tank like that alive and something tells me Lowfyr would have no problem with that either - just had some bad moments, Ritchot had a really shitty way of dealing with it and therefore Lowfyr choose to attack him, and since this is VCC R&amp;F, it is really convenient to make a cheapshot at his gear. A bit sad that everybody jumped on the bandwagon. <br>
