It is the only class where gear is what makes you a good/bad player. When I applied to CC and was in tells with Baldrik about my chances of making it in he asked me &quot; are you a good tank?&quot; I replied I sucked less than most but couldnt compare to any tanks already in CC. Why? Because of the gear. I wasnt any less of a talent or knew my role any less I just didnt have the opportunity to obtain the gear it took to make a truly fine warrior.<br>
<br>
Dont get me wrong there are some finer points in tanking that are definately learned but they dont apply really to a group that is grinding xp.<br>
<br>
Not having the finest gear available but far from gimp I can tell you that fucking grinding xp in PoV was fucking nerve wracking for me. The whole success of the group basically was on my not so well geared toon and everytime my cleric/shaman/chanter got aggro the panic I would feel sometimes was truly fucked up.<br>
<br>
One other quick point I would like to point out that if you were never on a tanks side of the taunt button you may not know THEY FAIL SOMETIMES. Thats right just like a monks fd they fucking fail. But guess what, you dont get a neat little failure message. There is nothing more frustrating than SLAMMING THAT FUCKING TAUNT BUTTON and having some pally in your group pop off with &quot;wtb taunt&quot; or a shaman saying &quot;battle shammy in action&quot;. /grrr <br>
<br>
Now I know Lowf you didnt bring this to R&amp;F because you had a gimp tank. You did it cuz he was a fucktard. <br>
<br>
But I am sure that alot of tanks will agree that Sony needs to fix a warriors role in the game. Our &quot;role&quot; is to obtain and maintain aggro. Thats it. The end. The whole reason warriors are even in the game. Dont you think we should be the best at it at least? <br>
<br>
